Description.
Female. Small and slender species. Occiput smooth; fastigium of vertex about 1.6 times as broad as scape; scape as long as eye; pedicel about half length of scape. Eyes ovoid (
Fig. 2A
). Ocelli ovoid; median ocellus very large, well developed; lateral ocelli longer than wide, facing laterally (
Fig. 2A
). Anterior margin of pronotum slightly projecting in the middle, posterior margin nearly straight; lateral lobes longer than deep, ventral margin straight (
Fig. 1
; 
Fig. 2B
). Tegmina extremely short, only reaching the middle area of fourth abdominal tergite; hind wings about half as long as tegmina.

Fore coxa with a spine at fore margin (
Fig. 1C
); fore and mid femora unarmed (
Fig. 1
AB); fore and mid tibiae dorsally unarmed (
Fig. 2E
); fore tibiae ventrally with 4 external and 3 internal spines and one pair of smaller spurs; mid tibiae ventrally with 4 pairs of spines and one pair of smaller spurs; hind femora ventrally with 4 external spinules; hind tibiae dorsally with 6 internal spinules, 3–6 external spinules and one pair of apical spurs, ventrally with one preapical spines and 2 apical spurs on both sides (
Fig. 1E
).

Seventh abdominal sternite wide with a slightly elevated central area, forming a pair of lateral lobes, between them with a wide groove in midline. Subgenital plate transverse, very short especially in middle, pressed against seventh sternite with basal margin concave, giving room for the extension of seventh sternite Ovipositor curved upward strongly, dorsal margin and ventral margin smooth, apex acute (
Fig. 2N
).

(
Figs. 5–9
)

Description.
Male. Small and slender species. Occiput smooth; fastigium of vertex about 1.8 times as broad as scape; scape as long as eye; pedicel about half length of scape. Eyes ovoid (
Fig. 5A
). Ocelli indistinct. Anterior margin of pronotum convex in the middle, posterior margin generally convex; lateral lobes longer than deep, ventral margin nearly straight (
Fig. 5C
). Tegmina mesopterous, reaching posterior margin of eighth abdominal tergite; hind wings as long as tegmina.
